commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to Holder, no run ridiculously good slower ball. He needs to pull the length back, seeing Holder advance, and then put the cut on the ball to bear the leading edge as the batsman looks for midwicket because he has no other choice. The ball pitches outside leg stump. Instinct tells him to go against the cut and that's where the Fizz is so good. He makes them play against the cut all the time

Looked good for a third hundred in four ODIs, but he has to walk back now.

commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza to Holder, OUT caught behind again! He didn't begin the day very well, but he's ending it #LikeABoss! This round the wicket angle is working a treat. Keeps cramping the right-handers. And on the odd occasion he takes the ball across them, they keep playing horizontal bat shots and nicking behind. Hope fell to the pull, Holder falls to the cut. West Indies have been poor in executing their big shots this innings. #Bizarre

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Allen, OUT pins him in front. Lovely response from Shakib. The typical left-arm spinner's delivery. Angled in from round the wicket and straightening just enough that it strikes the pad and not the bat of a batsman playing for turn. Allen has a stride in, but this should hit the stump. Shave leg stump at least. Umpire Kettleborough seems to think so, at least but we don't have DRS in this series for confirmation of that

commentary: Mustafizur Rahman to Nurse, OUT goes high but not long and Sabbir is under that at deep midwicket; he's had a good day in the field and he wraps it up with a fine catch. Mustafizur strikes again, thanks to that brilliant slower ball. Pitches on leg stump. The batsman is too early into the shot and loses his shape. That's why it goes so high instead of long and well... the rest is fairly basic

He's not to the pitch of the ball, having come down the track too early and giving Nurse the opportunity to change his length, and also go tight into his pads. commentary: Nurse to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run has Mithun been run out?! Oooh, it's close, but he's just in. Very risky run from Mushfiqur, but he likes to keep things ticking, especially after quick wickets. And though that's a good idea, dinking the ball so close to a very good fielder like Jonathan Carter at first slip is asking for trouble. He runs to his right, to where short point would be, dives head-first at the ball, grabs it with his right hand and then flicks it, while he's still suspended in the air, under his body at the keeper. Epic fielding skillz

commentary: Allen to Mohammad Mithun, no run Mithun should have been run out. He goes for a reverse sweep and just sets off. Not realising Nurse is onto the ball quickly, moving to his left. Mushfiqur is aware of it though and, after taking a couple of steps forward, yells no and at that point, Mithun loses his footing and falls on his backside. He's stranded in the middle of the pitch with no way back. All Nurse has to do is lob the ball to the keeper... and he messes it up, sending it way over the keeper

commentary: Reifer to Mohammad Mithun, FOUR runs dropped... essentially because Roach misjudges a simple catch at deep square leg. He comes forward as Mithun pulls the ball, underestimating the power on the shot. had he stayed on the boundary, it would've been a dolly. Could've been a maiden ODI wicket for Reifer. And a game-breaking one at that
